The paper proposes a deep neural architecture for time series forecasting using deep learning, which is a common topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence research (cs.LG, cs.AI). The architecture includes residual links and fully-connected layers, which are common components in neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also tests the proposed architecture on several datasets, including tourism data, which could fall under computer vision (cs.CV) or data science (cs.DS) sub-categories.
